def: The inclination or deviation from the vertical of any mineralvein.
A musical wind instrument, now used chiefly in the Highlands ofScotland.
The pedicel raising the pistil or ovary above the stamens, asin the passion flower. Lindley.
They go out, or retire from the scene; as, exeunt all exceptHamlet. See 1st Exit.
That may be demurred to. Stormonth.
A feldspar closely related to orthoclase, but triclinic. It ischiefly a silicate of sodium, potassium, and aluminium. Sp. gr., 2.57-- 2.60.
The state or quality of being crisp.
Belonging to, or in the style of, Tully (Marcus TulliusCicero).
Communicable by contact, by a virus, or by a bodily exhalation;catching; as, a contagious disease.
Pertaining to heralds, declarations of war, and treaties ofpeace; as, fecial law. Kent.
